The paper deals with explaining the behavior of deep learning models for image similarity tasks, which involves semantic feature representation rather than classification. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes an explanation method that pairs a saliency map with an attribute, which involves techniques from Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with image datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves attribute recognition, which suggests that it may belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
